standstill while the Gold Wasp that was hiding in the entrance fried him to a crisp!! Dia made it in and tied as I started running from the AB lifstone, to Baishi and then onto Lin to meet up with Dia. By now the storm here was really bad so I asked Dia to wait for me for 30 minutes as I quickly logged off. We really got hammered by a big hail storm and the lights flickered several times as I prayed that we wouldn't lose power so I could get back in game and get my corpse. About 30 minutes later I was in and meeting Dia in Lin. We portalled to our little buffing place and got ready for the last run as I tied to the portal. When we got up top we saw several people running towards the Acid Vault so we followed. I made it inside rather quickly but Dia got hit with several bad debuffs and didn't enter right away. Inside the place looked like a battlefield!!! Dead bugs, players and junk littered the ground. From what I had read in the past there was a safe spot near the portal in entrance but apparently that has all changed as a horde of bugs came boiling up from the tunnels. people were dropping left and right and with a 5% penalty already on me I dropped as well. I quickly portalled back and then ran back to the nest to get my gear. Dia was the only one there and she was buffing as a bug came up from the tunnels and started nailing her. I started shooting but wasn't buffed at all so was only hitting for 10 points a pop. I was quickly squashed again!!! Now at 15% penalty I portalled one last time and ran back for my gear. I got very lucky I didn't die on the run, got my gear and called it a night.<br>
